I’d like to make an official announcement! I am making my Pro Debut on June 23rd at the @livecasinophl. I’ve signed a pro contract with @art_of_war_cage_fighting and I’m looking forward to a very fruitful career in MMA. Specifically I would like to mention everyone at @balancemma @animalblackbelt @jiujitsumatrix Coach Andy for sticking with me and building me up to the fighter I am today. Thank you coach Isaac at the @matfactorywrestlingclub for always helping me better myself in the wrestling room and in life through hard work and prayer. 🙏🏼 Thank you to D1 Brandon and everyone at @teamevolutionnaples @keithrummelre @cosmoalexandre for coaching me and building my wrestling and Muay Thai. I would also like to thank my boxing coaches @mickeyrosatijr and @frank.destefano.372 for introducing me to boxing and putting your time into me over the years. Thank you to my strength and conditioning coach @trainertrae33 for making me into a bull. Thank you @gianna.scavetti for helping me through every day. I am grateful to have all of my sponsors and fans in my corner since the beginning. I Love you all. This is just the beginning for us. 🙏🏼👊🏼🇮🇹😤

The main event of @rdr_boxing RDR Boxing's event tonight from the @clarionhotelphl Clarion Hotel in Essington, PA was a four-round battle of cruiserweights making their professional debut. 

@teamgarbarino John Garbarino, of Philadelphia, took on Elizabeth, NJ's @jonde_2496 De'Jon Farrell-Francis. 

The pro-Garbarino crowd was well entertained by this contest.  While both are in the developmental stages of their career, Garbarino threw more compact punches, which made him the more effective fighter. 

In the second Garbarino was able to knock Farrell-Francis down.  Farrell-Francis beat the count and was able to continue. 

Garbarino was able to continue to land effective blows in the round, like this face-raking left hook. 

Farrell-Francis survived the second round, and had a better second-half of the fight.  Garbarino slowed down, in the second half of the bout.  In the fourth round, this helped enable Farrell-Francis to do his best work of the bout. 

The bout went to the scorecards.  The official scores were 40-35, 40-35, and 38-37, all for Garbarino, the winner by unanimous decision. 

The Fight Photos scored the bout 39-36 Garbarino. 

Garbarino starts his pro boxing career with a win, his record 1-0.  Farrell-Francis is now 0-1. 

This entire event is available for on-demand replay from @bxng.tv BXNG's bxngtv.com website.
